    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-09T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-09T22:00:00-05:00" n="1002"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1002">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.797/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-10T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 10, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 10—4:29
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Cabinet approved August 9th for submission to the next session of the Diet a
                    draft bill for the control of the automobile industry with the following
                    pertinent provisions.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The imposition of a license system for assembling automobiles and the
                        manufacture of parts.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Licenses will be granted only to companies organized under Japanese law
                        and whose majority of stock is held by Japanese subjects.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Companies already established will not be affected to the extent of
                        present production capacity but any extension or expansion in equipment or
                        output facilities will be subject to control under the new law.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Further details contained in despatch No. 1431 today’s pouch.<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d1002fn16">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Please notify Department of Commerce.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
